RACE.RACE_TEXT: AQUEDUCT RACE 1 1M Dirt CR: 74. Maiden Claiming Purse 43000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD FOALED IN NEW YORK STATE AND APPROVED BY THE NEW YORK STATE-BRED REGISTRY. Weight, 120 lbs. Claiming Price $40,000 (1.5% Aftercare Assessment Due At Time Of Claim Otherwise Claim Will Be Void).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FIRE KING went to the front, was well rated while setting a moderate pace, dictated terms while inside to the two path around the turn, responded well when set down into upper stretch and proved much the best under strong urging. TWO CHUCKLES broke in and brushed with a foe, settled on the outside, chased four then three wide around the turn, pursued the winner in the stretch and was second best. CONNECT THE BROCKS veered in at the start, was taken under a tight hold early then settled, moved closer near the nine-sixteenths, dropped back while inside under urging early on the turn then moved to the two to three path, turned into the stretch in the two path, moved out around the three-sixteenths, remained on his inside lead in the drive and secured the show. LAUREL VALLEY was rated just off the pace, dropped back in the two path around the turn and came up empty. CAMPBELITO lost his footing at the start and was off slow, dropped well behind under urging, went around the turn in the three path and was no factor. SOMAMA BEACH was brushed by a rival at the start, stalked the pace on the outside under a very tight hold, was let out late on the backstretch, chased three wide around the turn and faltered.

ENTRY.NAME: Connect the Brocks
ENTRY.COMMENT: veered in start,in hand early,urged ins-3path turn,mvd out,up3rd

ENTRY.NAME: Laurel Valley
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated just off pace,dropped back 2path turn,empty

ENTRY.NAME: Campbelito
ENTRY.COMMENT: lost footing start, off slow, urged at rear, 3p turn, no factor

RACE.RACE_TEXT: AQUEDUCT RACE 2 1 1/8M Dirt CR: 81. Claiming Purse 36000. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since July 1 Allowed 3 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000 (1.5% Aftercare Assessment Due At Time Of Claim Otherwise Claim Will Be Void).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HANG TIGHT settled on the inside, moved closer outside the five-eighths, chased inside early on the far turn, shifted three wide at the five-sixteenths, gained to make a bid at the quarter-pole, fought with the runner-up to the wire and prevailed under strong urging. OPEN TIL MIDNIGHT was hustled from the gate, went around the first turn in the three path, tracked the pace, moved closer outside the five-eighths, chased three then four wide on the far turn, made a bid at the quarter-pole, dueled with the winner to the wire and missed while able to get the place. STRONG LIGHT broke out and was last to commence, went four wide on the first turn, settled on the outside, was urged four then five wide on the far turn, chased the leading duo outside in the stretch, gained into the final sixteenth but missed while clear for the show. MAILMAN'S A FLYER had a shoe repaired in the paddock then had his saddle adjusted behind the gate, went two to three wide around the first turn, settled off the pace, came under intermittent urging late on the backstretch, fell to the rear while moving from the two path to the rail around the far turn and lacked the needed response. KONG LOVES A FIGHT dropped from the two path to near the rail under restraint around the opening bend, was reserved off the pace, moved out near the five-eighths, was roused while three then two wide on the final turn, shifted four wide into the stretch and lacked the needed kick. MOONSHININGBRIGHT was hustled to the front, showed the way in the two path with a clear advantage, was asked near the quarter-pole, lost the lead into upper stretch and gave way.

ENTRY.NAME: Mailman's a Flyer
ENTRY.OWNER: Cash Norman L and Cash Lola

ENTRY.NAME: Strong Light
ENTRY.OWNER: Three Player's Stable and Barrera III Oscar S

RACE.RACE_TEXT: AQUEDUCT RACE 3 7F Dirt CR: 70. Maiden Claiming Purse 35000. FOR MAIDENS, FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD FOALED IN NEW YORK STATE AND APPROVED BY THE NEW YORK STATE-BRED REGISTRY. Weight, 122 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000 (1.5% Aftercare Assessment Due At Time Of Claim Otherwise Claim Will Be Void).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: OUR SON JAKE pressed the pace on the outside, took the lead leaving the backstretch, shook clear in the two path around the turn, cruised into upper stretch under his own power, responded well when asked near the furlong marker, came under a right-handed crop coming to the sixteenth-pole and maintained a safe advantage. MAKART settled off the pace, was roused while moving from the two path to the four path around the turn, remained on his inside lead in the stretch and secured the place. TYRANNOSAURUS REX was hustled from the gate, stalked the pace on the outside, moved from three to five wide around the turn and came up empty while best of the rest. BRENNAN'S WAR moved out then settled on the outside, was urged along late on the backstretch, chased three wide around the turn and tired. DEVIL'S EDGE set the pace under pressure to his outside, lost the lead while inside into the turn and faded.

ENTRY.NAME: Devil's Edge
ENTRY.COMMENT: set pressured pace, headed 7/16, inside, faded

RACE.RACE_TEXT: AQUEDUCT RACE 4 6F Dirt CR: 90. Claiming Purse 60000. (UP TO $10,440 NYSBFOA) FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since July 1 Allowed 3 lbs. Claiming Price $40,000 (Maiden And Claiming Races For $32,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances) (1.5% Aftercar e Assessment Due At Time Of Claim Otherwise Claim Will Be Void).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HYDRA settled off the pace, drafted three wide around the turn, turned into the stretch behind foes, altered to the five path at the three-sixteenths, rallied into the final furlong, closed well to make a bid near the sixteenth-pole and got up under strong urging. CUSTOMEREXPERIENCE broke a half-step slow then dropped in tight between foes, settled at the rear, went around most of the turn in the two path, shifted four wide late on that bend, waited behind horses coming to the quarter-pole, altered to the six path at the three-sixteenths, rallied outside into the final furlong, closed well to make a bid alongside the winner into the final sixteenth but missed while able to get the place. BABA was away alertly then guided in while in front, showed the way down the backstretch, was asked in the two path on the turn, extended the advantage under a drive in upper stretch, led to the sixteenth-pole then was overtaken while clear for the show. GAME THEORY lost her footing slightly at the start, moved up then pressed the pace between horses, vied in the three path around the turn and tired. BLUE PAYNT was hustled from the gate, moved up to press the pace on the outside, vied four wide on the turn and weakened. DIVA BANKER settled just off the pace on the inside, was asked near the five-sixteenths and came up empty. SARATOGA BEAUTY tossed her head at the start and was off a step slow, settled on the outside, chased five wide around the turn and capitulated.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: AMERICAN LAW settled off the pace, was roused while inside to the two path around the turn, rallied into upper stretch, gained a short lead approaching the furlong marker and edged clear under strong urging. VODKA MARDINI was hustled to the front, showed the way down the backstretch, vied inside on the turn, was asked for his best in upper stretch, lost the lead to the winner coming to the furlong marker and was outfinished while clear for the place. MAGICAL WAYS broke out at the start, switched outside the leader early, moved up to press the pace with five furlongs to run, vied in the two to three path while asked on the turn, dropped back into upper stretch and weakened but earned the show. IMPROPER dropped back under urging, was coaxed along on the outside, went four wide around the turn and came up empty. NORGAY broke a step slow, was coaxed along at the rear, raced between foes passing the five-eighths, went three wide under urging around most of the turn, dropped to the two path late on that bend and failed to respond.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: HAPPY SOPHIA brushed with a foe at the start while off a bit slow, was hard held while tugging at the bit, traveled around the turn in the two path, was asked near the five-sixteenths, rallied in upper stretch, closed well to get the lead outside the sixteenth-pole then moved clear under steady urging. VALLELUJAH settled on the outside, ranged up early on the turn then was asked four wide, gained to make a bid into upper stretch, led into the final furlong but was overtaken while clear for the place. RIBOT'S VALENTINE tracked the leading duo on the outside, was asked three wide on the turn, chased four wide into the stretch then moved out while dropping back around the three-sixteenths and weakened but was clear for the show. CARAMOCHA brushed with a rival while off slow, spotted the front a few lengths, was urged alon on the outside, went four wide on the turn and lacked the needed response. SPIN A YARN disputed the pace on the outside, moved clear leaving the backstretch, went around the turn in the two path, was asked three wide into the stretch, lost the lead to the runner-up outside the furlong marker and tired. PATRIA contested the pace on the inside, dropped back leaving the backstretch and stopped.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: WARRIORS REVENGE broke in then was hustled, had the rider lose his left iron briefly before reaching down to regain footing, pressed the pace on the outside then in the three path around the turn, took the lead at the quarter-pole, shook clear into the final furlong and drew away under steady urging. WRITER'S REGRET broke in at the start, tracked the pace on the outside, chased four wide around the turn and narrowly earned the place while no match for the winner. ZIRCON was sent hard to the front, showed the way on the inside, lost the lead at the quarter-pole, dropped back into the final furlong and weakened then lost the place while able to hold the show. UNO was urged along off the pace, chased in the two path around the turn, turned into upper stretch under a drive and lacked the needed kick. DAUFUSKIE ISLAND broke out and hit the gate, settled off the pace, was urged four then five wide on the turn and lacked the needed response. SAFALOW'S MISSION was hustled from the gate but lacked speed, angled in near the five-eighths, saved ground around the turn, came out into the stretch, moved further out around the sixteenth-pole and failed to threaten. DEE BO broke awkwardly and was off a bit slow, settled off the pace, dropped back three wide on the turn, remained on his inside lead in the stretch and was no factor.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Say Florida Sandy S. AQUEDUCT RACE 8 7F Dirt CR: 107. Stakes Purse 100000. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD FOALED IN NEW YORK STATE AND APPROVED BY THE NEW YORK STATE-BRED REGISTRY. Non-Lasix Race pursuant to 4043.2 (7)(e)(5) Lasix not permitted within 48 hours of post time. By subscription of $100 each which should accompany the nominations; $500 to pass the entry box and an additional $500 to start. For horses not originally nominated, a supplemental nomination payment of $1,000 in addition to the entry and starting fees can be made at any time prior to the closing of entries.T he purse to be divided 55% to the owner of the winner, 20% to second, 12% to third, 6% to fourth, 4% to fifth and 3% divided equally amongst the remaining finishers. Weight, 124 lbs. Non-winners of a Sweepstake since June 1, 2022 allowed 2 lbs.; of a Swee epstake in 2022-23 allowed 4 lbs.; of two races other than maiden, claiming, starter or State-Bred Allowance since June 1, 2022 allowed 6 lbs. A trophy will be presented to the winning owner. Closed Monday, December 26, 2022 with 12 Nominations.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WUDDA U THINK NOW was hustled from the start, set the pace under pressure to his outside, vied along the rail on the turn, responded well under pressure while off the rail in the stretch and held gamely under strong urging. MARKET ALERT was reluctant to load, pressed the pace on the outside, drew even leaving the backstretch, vied in the three path around the turn, kept on in pursuit of the winner in the stretch and narrowly earned the place. BANKIT tracked the pace on the outside, chased four wide on the turn, made an outside bid in upper stretch, battled outside the top two in the final furlong and just missed the place while clear for the show. MY BOY TATE settled under some urging, was roused in the two path on the turn, angled out in upper stretch and lacked the needed response. REGGAE MUSIC MAN broke through the front of the gate prior to the start but remained in the stall, was off a step slow, was urged along at the rear, went four wide on the turn, came five wide into upper stretch and failed to rally.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: CHEEKY TICO broke in and hit gate, was well placed in third position, went three wide on the turn, was roused coming to the five-sixteenths, rallied four wide into the stretch, closed well to take the lead inside the furlong marker and proved best under strong urging. DADS GOOD RUNNER was forced in at the start, pressed the pace on the outside, was urged along in the two path around the turn, gained the lead outside the furlong marker, fought with NAKED AND FAMOUS in upper stretch, bumped with that foe near the furlong marker, fought with the winner into the final sixteenth and missed while clear for the place. NAKED AND FAMOUS was hustled from the gate, set the pace under pressure, vied along the rail on the turn, lost the lead outside the quarter-pole, fought on in upper stretch, bumped with a rival nearing the eighth-pole and weakened but held the show. PAPI ON ICE bumped with a rival shortly after the start, was urged along off the pace, went four then five wide on the turn, came six wide into the stretch and gained ground but failed to impact. DOWNTOWN CONNECTOR settled off the pace, was urged along passing the half-mile pole, saved ground on the turn, came out at the quarter-pole and failed to rally. GOLDEN PURCHASE bumped with a rival just after the start, was urged along off the pace, went three then four wide on the turn, came five wide into the stretch, raced between foes into the final furlong and failed to threaten.
